\v 28 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* person \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* [\w true|strong="G3588"\w*] \w Jew|strong="G2453"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \it only\it* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w outwardly|strong="G1722"\w*, \w nor|strong="G3761"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* [\w true|strong="G3588"\w*] \w circumcision|strong="G4061"\w* \w something|strong="G1510"\w* \w outward|strong="G5318"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w flesh|strong="G4561"\w*;  
\v 29 \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jew|strong="G2453"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3739"\w* \w inwardly|strong="G2927"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w circumcision|strong="G4061"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w heart|strong="G2588"\w*—\w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w letter|strong="G1121"\w*—\w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w praise|strong="G1868"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 2:29 \ft God looks on the heart. Those who worship Him must do so ‘in spirit and in truth’ (John 4:23-24). We do not choose who will procreate us, nor does a baby boy choose to be circumcised, so such factors cannot guarantee God's acceptance.\f*   
\c 3  
\s1 Advantage  
\m
\v 1 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w advantage|strong="G4053"\w* \w does|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jew|strong="G2453"\w* \w have|strong="G5101"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w profit|strong="G5622"\w* \w of|strong="G2228"\w* \w circumcision|strong="G4061"\w*?  
\v 2 \w Much|strong="G4183"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w way|strong="G5158"\w*!\f + \fr 3:2 \ft For a fuller list of the advantages, see Romans 9:1-5. To be born into a culture that has been blessed with God's Light is certainly an advantage.\f* \w First|strong="G4413"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w entrusted|strong="G4100"\w* \w with|strong="G2316"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w oracles|strong="G3051"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 3:2 \ft Job was written by a pre-Jew, but all the rest of the Old Testament, which is what Paul is referring to, was written by Jews. For that matter, all the books of the New Testament were also written by Jews (with the possible exception of Luke). “The oracles of God” are God's written Revelation to the human race.\f*  
\v 3 \w So|strong="G3361"\w*, \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* \w did|strong="G5101"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w believe|strong="G4102"\w*? \w Their|strong="G3588"\w* unbelief \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w nullify|strong="G2673"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w faithfulness|strong="G4102"\w*, \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w it|strong="G1063"\w*?  
\v 4 \w Of|strong="G3056"\w* course \w not|strong="G3361"\w*! \w Rather|strong="G1161"\w*, \w let|strong="G1096"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w found|strong="G1096"\w* \w true|strong="G3588"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w man|strong="G3956"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w liar|strong="G5583"\w*; \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w*:  
\q1 “\w That|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w words|strong="G3056"\w*,  
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w overcome|strong="G3528"\w* \w when|strong="G1161"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w judged|strong="G2919"\w*.”\f + \fr 3:4 \ft See Psalm 51:4. “If we are faithless, He remains faithful—He is incapable of denying Himself” (2 Timothy 2:13).\f*   
\s2 A conundrum  
\p
\v 5 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* unrighteousness highlights \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w*, \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w shall|strong="G2316"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*? \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* unrighteous \w for|strong="G1161"\w* inflicting \w His|strong="G2596"\w* \w wrath|strong="G3709"\w*, \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w*? (\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w speak|strong="G3004"\w* \w as|strong="G1161"\w* \w a|strong="G1487"\w* \w man|strong="G3361"\w*.)  
\v 6 \w Of|strong="G2316"\w* course \w not|strong="G3361"\w*! \w Otherwise|strong="G1893"\w*, \w how|strong="G4459"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w judge|strong="G2919"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*?  
\v 7 \w Still|strong="G2089"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* truth \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w abounded|strong="G4052"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* falsehood, \w just|strong="G5613"\w* \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w am|strong="G2504"\w* \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w still|strong="G2089"\w* \w judged|strong="G2919"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* sinner?\f + \fr 3:7 \ft If I choose falsehood, it is an evil choice, and I deserve to be punished, quite apart from any highlighting of God's righteousness. Any ‘highlighting’ does not alter the nature of my choice.\f*  
\v 8 However, \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w must|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Let|strong="G1510"\w* \w us|strong="G3004"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w evil|strong="G2556"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w good|strong="G3588"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w*” (\w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w some|strong="G5100"\w* \w people|strong="G1510"\w* slanderously \w claim|strong="G5346"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w*)—\w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w condemnation|strong="G2917"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w well|strong="G2532"\w* deserved!\f + \fr 3:8 \ft I suppose that part of the point is that all evil has consequences in this life and in this world, and any eventual ‘good’ does not undo those consequences, and neither does it compensate for them.\f*   
\s1 All are under sin  
\p
\v 9 \w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*? \w Are|strong="G1510"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w any|strong="G3956"\w* \w better|strong="G4284"\w*? \w Not|strong="G3756"\w* \w at|strong="G3756"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*! \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w already|strong="G4256"\w* \w charged|strong="G4256"\w* \w both|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Greeks|strong="G1672"\w*\f + \fr 3:9 \ft Paul uses ‘Greeks’ as a cover term for all non-Jews.\f* \w that|strong="G3956"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w under|strong="G5259"\w* sin.  
