\s1 Righteousness by faith  
\p
\v 21 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \nd \+w now|strong="G1161"\+w*\nd*, \w apart|strong="G5565"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w revealed|strong="G5319"\w*, \w being|strong="G2532"\w* \w attested|strong="G3140"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Law|strong="G3551"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Prophets|strong="G4396"\w*,  
\v 22 namely, \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w from|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G1519"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*\f + \fr 3:22 \ft That righteousness is available to all, but is only applied to those who believe. Perhaps 7% of the Greek MSS omit “and upon all”, to be followed by NIV, NASB, TEV, LB, etc.—an inferior proceeding (it is an easy case of ‘similar ending’—the eye of the copyist skipped from one ‘all’ to the next).\f* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w*. \w There|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w difference|strong="G1293"\w*:  
\v 23 \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* sinned \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w fall|strong="G5302"\w* \w short|strong="G5302"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*,\f + \fr 3:23 \ft What do you think ‘the glory of God’ refers to? In this context it can scarcely be brilliance or effulgence. I suggest that God's true glory is what He Himself \+bd \+nd is\+nd*\+bd*, His essence—truth, holiness, justice, love, among others. Although pristine Adam presumably reflected that essence quite well, the Fall resulted in a barrier that man cannot cross, apart from divine assistance. I suspect that modern man is but a poor reflection of what pristine Adam once was (due to accumulated congenital weaknesses). Alas, we fall far short!\f*  
\v 24 \w being|strong="G5547"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w* \w freely|strong="G1432"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* redemption \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*;  
\v 25 \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* openly \w made|strong="G2316"\w* available \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G1519"\w* \w propitiation|strong="G2435"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* blood, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w demonstrate|strong="G1732"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* passing \w over|strong="G1519"\w*, \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s forbearance, \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w previously|strong="G4266"\w* \w committed|strong="G4266"\w* sins;\f + \fr 3:25 \ft “Without the shedding of blood there is no remission” (Hebrews 9:22). “When I see the blood, I will pass over you” (Exodus 12:13, 22-23). “Behold! The Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world!” (John 1:29). 1 Peter 1:18-20 states that the Lamb, with His blood shed, was so foreknown before the foundation of the world. All the animal blood shed in the Old Testament only covered sin; it did not pay for it. All those sacrifices looked forward to Christ's perfect sacrifice. But all of that was only validated by the death of God's Lamb. So as verse 25 here states, the true propitiation is now available “through the faith in His blood”. This propitiation also benefits the Old Testament saints.\f*  
\v 26 \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w demonstrate|strong="G1732"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w righteousness|strong="G1343"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w present|strong="G3568"\w* \w time|strong="G2540"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w just|strong="G1342"\w*, \w Himself|strong="G1519"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w justifier|strong="G1344"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.\f + \fr 3:26 \ft I take the reference to be to the Faith that revolves around the person and work of Jesus.\f*   
\p
\v 27 \w Where|strong="G4226"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w boasting|strong="G2746"\w*? \w It|strong="G1223"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w excluded|strong="G1576"\w*. \w By|strong="G1223"\w* \w what|strong="G4169"\w* \w kind|strong="G4169"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w*? \nd \+w No|strong="G3780"\+w*\nd*, \w but|strong="G3767"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w a|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*.  
\v 28 \w Therefore|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* conclude \w that|strong="G1063"\w* \w a|strong="G2041"\w* person \w is|strong="G4102"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w* \w by|strong="G1344"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w apart|strong="G5565"\w* \w from|strong="G5565"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G3551"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*.  
\v 29 \w Or|strong="G2228"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w only|strong="G3440"\w*? \w Is|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3780"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w*? \w Yes|strong="G3483"\w*, \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w*,  
\v 30 \w since|strong="G1537"\w* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w only|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w justify|strong="G1344"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w circumcised|strong="G4061"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* uncircumcised \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Faith|strong="G4102"\w*.\f + \fr 3:30 \ft How could a ritual performed on a baby justify that baby? A circumcised person had to demonstrate faith in God by shedding animal blood to cover his sin; this before the perfect Sacrifice. Now justification comes through \+nd the\+nd* Faith.\f*  
\v 31 \w Do|strong="G1096"\w* \w we|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w nullify|strong="G2673"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w Faith|strong="G4102"\w*? \w Of|strong="G1223"\w* course \w not|strong="G3361"\w*! Rather, \w we|strong="G3767"\w* \w uphold|strong="G2476"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*.\f + \fr 3:31 \ft The proper function of the law is recognized within the Faith.\f*   
\c 4  
