\s2 Indwelling sin  
\p
\v 13 \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w has|strong="G1096"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w good|strong="G1223"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*? \w Of|strong="G1223"\w* course \w not|strong="G3361"\w*! Rather \w the|strong="G1223"\w* sin, \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w it|strong="G1223"\w* \w might|strong="G1785"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* exposed \w as|strong="G2596"\w* sin, \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w producing|strong="G2716"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w in|strong="G2596"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w what|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w good|strong="G1223"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w commandment|strong="G1785"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* sin \w might|strong="G1785"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* extremely sinful.  
\v 14 \w We|strong="G3754"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w spiritual|strong="G4152"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* fleshly, \w having|strong="G1492"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* ‘\w sold|strong="G4097"\w*’ \w under|strong="G5259"\w* sin\f + \fr 7:14 \ft A person who was sold became a slave ‘under’ a new owner, so I take Paul's point to be that sin is giving the orders.\f*  
\v 15 —\w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w see|strong="G1097"\w*, \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w understand|strong="G1097"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w am|strong="G2309"\w* \w doing|strong="G4160"\w*: \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w practice|strong="G4238"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2309"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w*, \w but|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w*!\f + \fr 7:15 \ft In this interesting passage Paul contrast his two natures. As an aid to the reader, I will attempt to identify the two natures throughout the passage. \fv 14\fv*\ft  We know that the law is spiritual, but I [old] am fleshly, having been ‘sold’ under sin \+fv 15\+fv*\ft —you see, I [new] do not understand what I am [old] doing: I [old] do not practice what I [new] want to do, but I [old] do what I [new] hate! \+fv 16\+fv*\ft  But if I [old] do what I [new] do not want to do, I [new] agree with the law that it is good. \+fv 17\+fv*\ft  So now it is no longer I [new] who am doing it, but the sin dwelling in me [both]. \+fv 18\+fv*\ft  Further, I [new] know that nothing good dwells in me [old], that is, in my flesh; because to will is present with me [new], but I [old] do not find how to perform the good. \+fv 19\+fv*\ft  Because I [old] do not do the good that I [new] want to do; rather I [old] practice the evil that I [new] do not want to do. \+fv 20\+fv*\ft  Now if I [old] do what I [new] do not want to do, it is no longer I [new] who do it, but the sin dwelling in me [both]. \+fv 21\+fv*\ft  So I [new] find this ‘law’, when I [new] want to do good, evil is right there with me [both]. \+fv 22\+fv*\ft  I [new] joyfully agree with God's law according to the inner man [new], \+fv 23\+fv*\ft  but I [new] see a different ‘law’ in my body parts [old], warring against the law of my mind [new] and taking me [both] captive to the law of the sin that is in my body parts [old]. \+fv 24\+fv*\ft  What a wretched man I am [both]! Who will deliver me [new] from this body of death [old]? \+fv 25\+fv*\ft  I thank God—through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, with the mind I myself [new] serve God's law, but with the flesh [old], sin's law.\f*  
\v 16 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w want|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2309"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w*, \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w agree|strong="G4852"\w* \w with|strong="G3756"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w*.  
\v 17 \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w no|strong="G3765"\w* \w longer|strong="G3765"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w doing|strong="G2716"\w* \w it|strong="G1161"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* sin dwelling \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.  
