\v 30 Further, \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w predestined|strong="G4309"\w*, \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w*, \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w justified|strong="G1344"\w*, \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w glorified|strong="G1392"\w*.\f + \fr 8:30 \ft All the verbs in verse 30 are in the past tense, reflecting God's sovereignty. Note the sequence: foreknowledge, predestination, calling, justification and glorification.\f*   
\s1 Summary to this point  
\p
\v 31 \w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w shall|strong="G2316"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w*? \w Since|strong="G2596"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w us|strong="G3004"\w*, \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w us|strong="G3004"\w*?  
