\v 4 \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Israelites|strong="G2475"\w*.\f + \fr 9:4 \ft Wow, Paul, do you really mean it? Perhaps he is reflecting God's sorrow.\f* \w To|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w belong|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w adoption|strong="G5206"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w covenants|strong="G1242"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w giving|strong="G3548"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w law|strong="G3548"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* temple \w service|strong="G2999"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w promises|strong="G1860"\w*.  
\v 5 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* patriarchs \w are|strong="G1510"\w* theirs, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w came|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* (\w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w physical|strong="G4561"\w* \w part|strong="G2596"\w*),\f + \fr 9:5 \ft Both “the Christ” and “who is over all” are in the masculine gender, separated by το κατα σαρκα, often rendered as ‘according to the flesh’. But the article, το, is in the neuter gender, and so must have a different referent. Paul is being precisely correct: it was only the physical part of the Messiah that came through Israel, the divine part did not.\f* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*, \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w forever|strong="G1519"\w* \w blessed|strong="G2128"\w*. Amen.   
\s1 Children of the promise  
\p
