\c 11  
\s1 The remnant  
\m
\v 1 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* reject \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w*, \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w*? \w Of|strong="G1537"\w* course \w not|strong="G3361"\w*! \w Why|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w myself|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w Israelite|strong="G2475"\w*, \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w seed|strong="G4690"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* Abraham, \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tribe|strong="G5443"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* Benjamin!\f + \fr 11:1 \ft Observe that Paul knew what tribe he belonged to; this at the beginning of the Christian era. If God would save Paul, then He is still saving Jews (and God knows what tribe they are from, even if they no longer do).\f*  
\v 2 \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* rejected \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w foreknew|strong="G4267"\w*. \w Do|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w about|strong="G5613"\w* \w Elijah|strong="G2243"\w*, \w how|strong="G5613"\w* \w he|strong="G3739"\w* appeals \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w Israel|strong="G2474"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*:  
\v 3 “\sc \+w Lord|strong="G2962"\+w*\sc*, \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* killed \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w prophets|strong="G4396"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w torn|strong="G2679"\w* \w down|strong="G2679"\w* \w your|strong="G2962"\w* \w altars|strong="G2379"\w*; \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w only|strong="G3441"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w left|strong="G5275"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w trying|strong="G2212"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w take|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G2212"\w* \w life|strong="G5590"\w*!”\f + \fr 11:3 \ft See 1 Kings 19:10,14.\f*  
\v 4 \w But|strong="G3588"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w does|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w divine|strong="G5538"\w* \w response|strong="G5538"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*? “\w I|strong="G3004"\w* \w have|strong="G3748"\w* \w reserved|strong="G2641"\w* \w for|strong="G3756"\w* \w myself|strong="G1683"\w* \w seven|strong="G2035"\w* \w thousand|strong="G2035"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 11:4 \ft The term here refers specifically to males.\f* \w who|strong="G5101"\w* \w have|strong="G3748"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w bowed|strong="G2578"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w knee|strong="G1119"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* Baal.”\f + \fr 11:4 \ft See 1 Kings 19:18. Evidently Elijah knew nothing about them, and perhaps each of them also thought he was the only one. I see a practical application here: I must never assume that what God is doing to and through me is the whole show, or even a major part of it. Now, much more than in Elijah's day, God is doing all sorts of interesting things all over the world!\f*  
\v 5 \w Even|strong="G2532"\w* \w so|strong="G3779"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3588"\w* \w present|strong="G3568"\w* \w time|strong="G2540"\w*, \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w remnant|strong="G3005"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w election|strong="G1589"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w*.  
