\v 12 \w The|strong="G1161"\w* \w night|strong="G3571"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* nearly over, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w near|strong="G1448"\w*;\f + \fr 13:12 \ft When a servant of Christ dies physically, he leaves the ‘night’ of this world behind and his ‘day’ of glory begins. Each day we live brings us closer to that moment, so we need to make the best possible use of the time we have left.\f* \w so|strong="G3767"\w* \w let|strong="G1161"\w* us get rid \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w darkness|strong="G4655"\w*, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w let|strong="G1161"\w* us \w put|strong="G1746"\w* \w on|strong="G1746"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w weapons|strong="G3696"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w light|strong="G5457"\w*.\f + \fr 13:12 \ft That is right, ‘weapons’. Light repels darkness. To make a difference, weapons must be used.\f*  
