\p
\v 19 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w let|strong="G3767"\w* \w us|strong="G1519"\w* \w pursue|strong="G1377"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* promote \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w by|strong="G2532"\w* \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w edify|strong="G3619"\w* \w another|strong="G3588"\w*.  
\v 20 \w Do|strong="G3361"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w destroy|strong="G2647"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w work|strong="G2041"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w sake|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w food|strong="G1033"\w*. \w All|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w indeed|strong="G3303"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* ‘\w clean|strong="G2513"\w*’; \w however|strong="G3303"\w* \w it|strong="G1223"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w wrong|strong="G2556"\w* \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w man|strong="G3956"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w gives|strong="G1223"\w* \w offence|strong="G4348"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w eating|strong="G2068"\w*.  
\v 21 \w It|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* \w eat|strong="G2068"\w* \w meat|strong="G2907"\w* \w nor|strong="G3366"\w* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w* \w wine|strong="G3631"\w* \w nor|strong="G3366"\w* \w do|strong="G3361"\w* \w anything|strong="G5315"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w your|strong="G1722"\w* brother \w stumbles|strong="G4350"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w offended|strong="G4624"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* weakened.\f + \fr 14:21 \ft “Or is offended, or is weakened” is omitted by 1.8% of the Greek manuscripts (of objectively inferior quality), to be followed by NIV, NASB, TEV, LB, etc.—an inferior proceeding.\f*   
\p
\v 22 \w Do|strong="G2919"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*? \w Have|strong="G2192"\w* \w it|strong="G3739"\w* \w privately|strong="G2596"\w* \w before|strong="G1799"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*. \w Happy|strong="G3107"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w he|strong="G3739"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w does|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w judge|strong="G2919"\w* \w himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w what|strong="G3739"\w* \w he|strong="G3739"\w* \w approves|strong="G1381"\w*.  
\v 23 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w eats|strong="G2068"\w* \w with|strong="G1537"\w* \w doubt|strong="G1252"\w* stands \w condemned|strong="G2632"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w*; \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w whatever|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* sin.\f + \fr 14:23 \ft Well now, faith would appear to be a rather important commodity! But just why is everything else ‘sin’? If the basic idea in ‘sin’ is to miss the mark, or to fall short (Romans 3:23), then faith is of the essence. Habakkuk 2:4, “the just shall live by faith”, is repeated three times in the New Testament—Romans 1:17, Galatians 3:11 and Hebrews 10:38. “That no one is justified by the law in the sight of God is evident, for ‘the just shall live by faith’ ” (Galatians 3:11). So to depend on the law (or any equation based on works) is to fall short. “But without faith it is impossible to please Him, for he who comes to God must believe that He exists, and that He is a rewarder of those who diligently seek Him” (Hebrews 11:6). If God demands faith, then anything else will fall short, will miss the mark.\f*   
\s1 Doxology  
\p
\v 24 Now to Him who has power to establish you according to my Gospel and the proclamation of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery kept secret through long ages,  
\v 25 but now revealed and made known through the prophetic Scriptures,\f + \fr 14:25 \ft Since it is being revealed ‘only now’, these ‘prophetic Scriptures’ must be New Testament writings, given by God!\f* according to the command of the eternal God, with a view to obedience of faith among all ethnic nations  
\v 26 —to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ—to Him be the glory forever! Amen.\f + \fr 14:26 \ft 5.2% of the Greek manuscripts place verses 24-26 at the end of the book, rather than here. Paul habitually places doxologies throughout his letters—they do not occur only at the end.\f*   
\c 15  
\s1 Summary  
\m
\v 1 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w strong|strong="G1415"\w* \w ought|strong="G3784"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w bear|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* limitations \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* weak, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* please \w ourselves|strong="G1438"\w*.  
