\q1 \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w place|strong="G1909"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w hope|strong="G1679"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.”\f + \fr 15:12 \ft See Isaiah 11:10.\f*   
\m
\v 13 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w* \w fill|strong="G4137"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w believing|strong="G4100"\w*,\f + \fr 15:13 \ft If one stops and thinks about it, ‘joy’ and ‘peace’ depend on believing—when we begin to doubt we lose both. Also, if you are filled with hope, you tend to have more ‘bounce’, you work with greater enthusiasm.\f* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w abound|strong="G4052"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w hope|strong="G1680"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.\f + \fr 15:13 \ft To abound by the power presumably means that we are to be doing things by that power. One does not ‘abound’ by sitting still doing nothing.\f*   
\s2 Paul's mission  
\p
\v 14 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w myself|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* really \w confident|strong="G3982"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w my|strong="G3956"\w* brothers, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w full|strong="G3324"\w* \w of|strong="G4012"\w* goodness, \w filled|strong="G4137"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w knowledge|strong="G1108"\w*, \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w admonish|strong="G3560"\w* \w others|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 15:14 \ft Instead of “others”, some 7% of the Greek manuscripts read ‘one another’, as in most versions.\f*  
\v 15 \w Nevertheless|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w to|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* quite \w boldly|strong="G5112"\w* \w on|strong="G1161"\w* \w some|strong="G3588"\w* \w points|strong="G3313"\w*, brothers, \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* reminder \w to|strong="G1325"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G5259"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w grace|strong="G5485"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*,  
\v 16 \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w should|strong="G2316"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w minister|strong="G3011"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w nations|strong="G1484"\w*, serving \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w priest|strong="G2418"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w* \w might|strong="G1484"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* \w an|strong="G1519"\w* \w acceptable|strong="G2144"\w* \w offering|strong="G4376"\w*,\f + \fr 15:16 \ft The concept is interesting: Paul is a priest, and the nations are his offering. I habitually present my own work to God as an offering.\f* sanctified \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.  
\v 17 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w I|strong="G3767"\w* \w do|strong="G2192"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* boast \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w pertaining|strong="G4314"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*;  
\v 18 \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w presume|strong="G5111"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w speak|strong="G2980"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w anything|strong="G5100"\w* \w except|strong="G3756"\w* \w those|strong="G3739"\w* \w things|strong="G3739"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w has|strong="G3739"\w* \w accomplished|strong="G2716"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w make|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Gentiles|strong="G1484"\w* \w obedient|strong="G5218"\w*—\w by|strong="G1223"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w deed|strong="G2041"\w*,  
\v 19 \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w signs|strong="G4592"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wonders|strong="G5059"\w*, \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w power|strong="G1411"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w fully|strong="G4137"\w* proclaimed\f + \fr 15:19 \ft Note the ‘word and \+nd deed\+nd*’, the ‘signs and wonders’. Can someone who has only ‘word’ claim to have ‘fully proclaimed’ the Gospel?\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Gospel|strong="G2098"\w* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2419"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w way|strong="G1722"\w* \w around|strong="G2945"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Illyricum|strong="G2437"\w*.\f + \fr 15:19 \ft Illyricum lies to the north of Macedonia, in what used to be Yugoslavia (a few decades ago).\f*  
\v 20 \w It|strong="G1161"\w* \w has|strong="G5547"\w* always \w been|strong="G3361"\w* \w my|strong="G3618"\w* aim \w to|strong="G2443"\w* evangelize \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w has|strong="G5547"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w been|strong="G3361"\w* \w named|strong="G3687"\w*, \w so|strong="G3779"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w would|strong="G5547"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* \w building|strong="G3618"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* someone \w else|strong="G3361"\w*'s \w foundation|strong="G2310"\w*;  
